 The Kebbi State Police Command, on Monday, said that 16 persons, and not 50, were killed by some yet-to-be-identified gunmen in the attack on Dankade village on Friday. The News Agency of Nigeria reports that some online media reported that no fewer than 50 people were killed during the attack on Dankade village in Danko/Wsaagu Local Government Area of Kebbi. The command’s Public Relations Officer, DSP Nafi’u Abubakar, who confirmed the figure in a telephone interview with NAN in Birnin Kebbi, said that 16 people, including a policeman and two soldiers were killed in the attack. He said, ”The incident happened on Friday around 3pm as the bandits coming from Zamfara State invaded the Dankade village and killed 13 civilians, one police officer and two soldiers. “On hearing of the invasion, the police patrol teams mobilised to the village and engaged them in a gun duel resulting in the loss of one of our officers and two army personnel. “Thirteen civilians were killed and we also eliminated unknown number of bandits in the duel.” Abubakar said that the bandits set some houses ablaze, adding that investigation had commenced into the incident. He urged members of the public to assist the command with relevant information to facilitate the arrest of the bandits. (NAN). 